
Overview

The Doctor Management System is a web application built with Node.js, Express.js, Passport.js, JWT, Bcrypt, and MongoDB. It provides a platform for users to log in, book appointments, view medical history, and contact the hospital. The admin section allows the addition of doctors, tracking salary history, managing hospital expenses, and adding new patients with their medical records.

Features
User Authentication: Secure login and registration system using Passport and JWT for user authentication.

Appointment Booking: Users can easily book appointments with doctors of their choice.

Medical History: Users have access to their medical history, allowing them to keep track of their health records.

Contact Hospital: Users can contact the hospital through the application for inquiries or assistance.

Admin Dashboard: Administrators have a dedicated dashboard to manage doctor lists, salary histories, and hospital expenses.

Patient Management: Admins can add new patients, including their medical records, for comprehensive healthcare management.

Email Notifications: Users receive email notifications using Nodemailer for appointment confirmations and other important updates.